<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/292660-what-does-closure-really-mean">What does closure really mean?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_292660'><a id="like_count_community_question_292660" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/292660?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">5 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F6596547-mockingbird">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/292660-what-does-closure-really-mean">7 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/292660-what-does-closure-really-mean">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/32743898-kaylan"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1466300948i/32743898._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/32743898-kaylan">Kaylan</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
closure (well, at least how they use it in the book) means a sense of conclusion, resolution or satisfaction at the end of an event/artistic work
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

